About the game for those who have not played yet:

"Munchkin" is a card adventure game based on a parody of role-playing games. The game's motto is "Kill the monsters, grab the treasure, backstab your friends!"üòÉ.

Role-playing game enthusiasts call players who are most concerned with making their character the coolest and most leveled-up, rather than enjoying playing together in a group, "Munchkins." 

The game is very fun: the pictures, the names of the monsters, the turns of phrase in the description, and even the rules‚Äîall of these create an atmosphere of humor and mockery of role-players.

If you and your company love role-playing games and know what character development is, then this game is genuinely for you.

This game is characterized by satirizing many elements of popular games, simple rules, and dynamism.

The players' goal is simple‚Äî"leveling up" their character in all possible and impossible ways (which is what all Munchkins are different for).

Victory goes to the one who first "levels up" their character to the 10th level... by any fair or even not so fair means‚Äîschemes, tricks, bluffing, and intrigue‚Äîthe game literally forces us to go through all of this.

The overall gameplay is based on an ordinary adventure‚ÄîMunchkins set out on a journey, encounter monsters, defeat them, capture treasures, increase their level, wait for the right moment, and backstab their opponents!

How to level up? It's simple: gain levels for defeated monsters, dress in gear, skillfully use special skills and various additional opportunities. Upon reaching the tenth level, the player wins.

text_entities.TRANSLATED_TEXT: On Thursday, December 26, I invite you to play 'Munchkinüòà'.

"Munchkin" is a card adventure game based on a parody of role-playing games. The game's slogan is "Kill the monsters, grab the treasure, stab your friends!"üòÉ.

In role-playing games, enthusiasts refer to players as munchkins, for whom the most important thing is to make their character the coolest and most leveled-up, rather than enjoying the joint game in the company.

The game is very fun: the pictures, monster names, expressions in the descriptions, and even the rules all create an atmosphere of humor and satire on role players.

If you and your company love role-playing games and know what leveling up a character means, the game is really for you.

This game is characterized by the mockery of many elements of famous games, simple rules, and dynamism.

The goal of the players is simple - to "level up" their character by all possible and impossible means (this is what distinguishes all munchkins).

Victory goes to the one who first "levels up" their hero to the 10th level... by any honest and not so honest means - manipulations, tricks, bluffing, and intrigues - the game literally forces us to go through all of this.

The overall gameplay is based on the usual adventure - munchkins go on a journey, meet monsters, defeat them, collect treasures, increase their level, wait for the right moment, and stab their rivals!

How to level up? It's simple: gain levels for defeated monsters, dress in gear, skillfully use special abilities and various additional opportunities. Once reaching the tenth level, the player wins.

The general gameplay is based on a normal adventure - munchkins go on a journey, encounter monsters, defeat them, take treasures, increase their level, wait for the right moment, and backstab rivals! Game "Codenames"

- is a team tabletop game focused on logic and associative thinking, which, shortly after its release, won all possible awards, including the Game of the Year award.

The backstory (plot basis) of the game: as a result of a hacker attack, the data of your intelligence agency got into the internet. Soon, everyone will know the code names of your agents. You need to quickly uncover your spies and come up with new code names for them. Time is short, so don't hesitate!

Game rules: players are divided into two teams ‚Äì blue and red. Each team chooses a captain. Both captains sit on one side of the table, while the rest of the players sit opposite them. Randomly, 25 cards with code names are selected and laid out on the table in a 5√ó5 grid.

Captains know which agents' names belong to which team and give clues to their teams, who try to find their agents faster. Giving a clue for each name is too time-consuming. Therefore, captains try to combine multiple names with a single clue. However, for the clue, the captain can use only one word that unites several names on the field and also mentions a number - how many names this clue unites.

As soon as a team player touches a card with a code name, the captain reveals the identity of this code name. If it's an agent belonging to their team, players continue guessing until they make a mistake or exhaust their attempts.

The team that manages to find all their agents first wins.

text_entities.TRANSLATED_TEXT: On Thursday, January 9, I'm inviting you to play 'Munchkinüòà'.

"Munchkin" is a card adventure game based on a parody of role-playing games. The game's motto is "Destroy monsters, grab treasures, betray your friends!" üòÉ.

Role-playing game enthusiasts call such players Munchkins, for whom the most important thing is to make their character the coolest and most leveled-up, rather than enjoying the shared game experience with the company.

The game is very fun: illustrations, monster names, verbal expressions in the descriptions, and even the rules - all these create an atmosphere of humor and mockery of role-players.

If you and your company love role-playing games and know what character leveling is, then this game is definitely for you.

This game is characterized by the satirical take on many elements of famous games, simple rules, and dynamism.

The goal of the players is simple - "leveling up" their character by all possible and impossible means (which is, essentially, what all munchkins are about).

Victory goes to the one who first "levels up" their hero to the 10th level... by any honest and even not so honest means ‚Äì trickery, cunning, bluffing and scheming - the game literally forces us to go through all this.

The overall gameplay is based on a typical adventure ‚Äì munchkins set out on a journey, encounter monsters, defeat them, take treasures, increase their level, wait for the right moment and betray rivals!

How to level up? It's simple: gain levels by defeating monsters, dress in gear, skillfully use special skills and various additional opportunities. Once the tenth level is reached, the player wins.
